mistral.reason: The calling code of Sri Lanka (IDD/country code) is +94, not the telephone numbers in Sri Lanka. Telephone numbers consist of aaa o nnnnnn where "aaa" represents the area code or mobile operator code, "o" represents the operator code for fixed numbers and "nnnnnn" is the 7-digit recipient number. The IDD/country code is used when calling from abroad to Sri Lanka.

gemma2.reason: Telephone numbers are a set of digits used for communication, while a calling code is a specific number used to dial internationally. These are distinct concepts.

qwen2.5.reason: The calling code refers to the country code for international calls (+94), not the entire telephone number format (aaa o nnnnnn) which includes area codes and subscriber numbers.
